<inglise> DIRECTIVE 98/78/EC OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL of 27 October 1998 on the supplementary supervision of insurance undertakings in an insurance group </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENDI JA N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 98/78/E&Uuml; kindlustusandjate gruppi kuuluvate kindlustusseltside t&auml;iendava j&auml;relevalve kohta 27. oktoober 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENT JA EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 57(2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 57 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 189b of the Treaty (3), </inglise>
<eesti> tegutsedes asutamislepingu artiklis 189b etten&auml;htud korras (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas the first Council Directive 73/239/EEC of 24 July 1973 on the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to the taking up and pursuit of the business of direct insurance other than life assurance (4) and the first Council Directive 79/267/EEC of 5 March 1979 on the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to the taking up and pursuit of the business of direct life assurance (5) require insurance undertakings to have solvency margins; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) vastavalt 24. juuli 1973. aasta esimesele n&otilde;ukogu direktiivile 73/239/EM&Uuml; otsekindlustustegevuse, v&auml;lja arvatud elukindlustustegevuse alustamise ja j&auml;tkamisega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta (4) ja 5. m&auml;rtsi 1979. aasta esimesele n&otilde;ukogu direktiivile 79/267/EM&Uuml; otsese elukindlustustegevuse alustamise ja j&auml;tkamisega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta (5) peavad kindlustusseltsidel olema solventsusmarginaalid; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas, under Council Directive 92/49/EEC of 18 June 1992 on the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to direct insurance other than life assurance and amending Directives 73/239/EEC and 88/357/EEC (6) and Council Directive 92/96/EEC of 10 November 1992 on the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to direct life assurance and amending Directives 79/267/EEC and 90/619/EEC (7) the taking up and the pursuit of the business of insurance are subject to the granting of a single official authorisation issued by the authorities of the Member State in which an insurance undertaking has its registered office (home Member State); whereas such authorisation allows an undertaking to carry on business throughout the Community, under either the right of establishment or the freedom to provide services; whereas the competent authorities of home Member States are responsible for monitoring the financial health of insurance undertakings, including their solvency; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu 18. juuni 1992. aasta direktiivile 92/49/EM&Uuml; otsekindlustusega, v&auml;lja arvatud elukindlustusega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta, millega muudetakse direktiive 73/239/EM&Uuml; ja 88/375/EM&Uuml;, (6) ja n&otilde;ukogu 10. novembri 1992. aasta direktiivile 92/96/EM&Uuml; otsese elukindlustusega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta, millega muudetakse direktiive 79/267/EM&Uuml; ja 90/619/EM&Uuml;, (7) on kindlustustegevuse alustamiseks ja j&auml;tkamiseks vaja &uuml;hte ametlikku tegevusluba, mille annavad v&auml;lja asutused liikmesriigis, kus on kindlustusseltsi registrij&auml;rgne asukoht (p&auml;ritoluliikmesriik); see tegevusluba v&otilde;imaldab kindlustusseltsil tegutseda kogu &uuml;henduses asutamis&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i teenuste osutamise vabaduse alusel; p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused vastutavad kindlustusseltside finantsseisundi, sealhulgas nende maksej&otilde;ulisuse j&auml;relevalve eest; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas measures concerning the supplementary supervision of insurance undertakings in an insurance group should enable the authorities supervising an insurance undertaking to form a more soundly based judgment of its financial situation; whereas such supplementary supervision should take into account certain undertakings which are not at present subject to supervision under Community Directives; whereas this Directive does not in any way imply that Member States are required to undertake supervision of those undertakings considered individually; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) kindlustusandjate gruppi kuuluvate kindlustusseltside t&auml;iendava j&auml;relevalve meetmed peaksid v&otilde;imaldama kindlustusseltside &uuml;le j&auml;relevalvet teostavatel asutustel teha kindlama otsuse nimetatud kindlustusseltside finantsseisundi kohta; t&auml;iendava j&auml;relevalve puhul tuleb arvesse v&otilde;tta ka teatavad ettev&otilde;tjad, kelle &uuml;le praegu &uuml;henduse direktiivide kohast j&auml;relevalvet ei teostata; k&auml;esolevas direktiivis ei eeldata mitte mingil juhul, et liikmesriigid peaksid teostama j&auml;relevalvet k&otilde;nealuste ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;le eraldi; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas insurance undertakings in a common insurance market engage in direct competition with each other and the rules concerning capital requirements must therefore be equivalent; whereas, to that end, the criteria applied to determine supplementary supervision must not be left solely to the discretion of Member States; whereas the adoption of common basic rules will be in the best interests of the Community in that it will prevent distortions of competition; whereas it is necessary to eliminate certain divergences between the laws of the Member States as regards the prudential rules to which insurance undertakings that are part of an insurance group are subject; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) kindlustusseltsid tegutsevad &uuml;hisel kindlustusturul &uuml;ksteisega otseselt konkureerides ja seet&otilde;ttu peavad kapitalin&otilde;udeid k&auml;sitlevad eeskirjad olema samav&auml;&auml;rsed; seep&auml;rast ei saa t&auml;iendava j&auml;relevalve m&auml;&auml;ratlemisel kasutatavate kriteeriumide &uuml;le lasta otsustada ainult liikmesriikidel; &uuml;histe p&otilde;hin&otilde;uete vastuv&otilde;tmine on igati &uuml;henduse huvides, sest see aitab v&auml;ltida konkurentsi moonutamist; k&otilde;rvaldada tuleb teatavad lahknevused liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide vahel, mis k&auml;sitlevad kindlustusandjate gruppi kuuluvate kindlustusseltside suhtes kohaldatavaid usaldatavusnormatiive; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas the approach adopted consists in bringing about such harmonisation as is essential, necessary and sufficient to achieve the mutual recognition of prudential control systems in this field; whereas the aim of this Directive is in particular to protect the interests of insured persons; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) vastuv&otilde;etud l&auml;henemisviisi kohaselt peab koosk&otilde;lastamine toimuma sellises ulatuses, mis on oluline, vajalik ja piisav, et saavutada k&otilde;nealuses valdkonnas usaldatavusnormatiivide t&auml;itmise kontrolli s&uuml;steemide vastastikune tunnustamine; k&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on eelk&otilde;ige kaitsta kindlustatud isikute huve; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas certain provisions of this Directive define minimum standards; whereas a home Member State may lay down stricter rules for insurance undertakings authorised by its own competent authorities; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) teatavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tted m&auml;&auml;ratlevad miinimumn&otilde;uded; p&auml;ritoluliikmesriik v&otilde;ib oma p&auml;devatelt asutustelt tegevusloa saanud kindlustusseltside suhtes kehtestada rangemad eeskirjad; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas this Directive provides for the supplementary supervision of any insurance company which is a participating undertaking in at least one insurance undertaking, reinsurance undertaking or non-member-country insurance undertaking and, under different rules, for the supplementary supervision of any insurance company whose parent undertaking is an insurance holding company, a reinsurance undertaking, a non-member-country insurance undertaking or a mixed-activity insurance holding company; whereas the supervision of individual insurance undertakings by the competent authorities remains the essential principle of insurance supervision; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) k&auml;esolevas direktiivis s&auml;testatakse k&otilde;igi selliste kindlustusseltside t&auml;iendav j&auml;relevalve, kes osalevad v&auml;hemalt &uuml;hes kindlustusseltsis, edasikindlustusseltsis v&otilde;i kolmanda riigi kindlustusseltsis, ja teistsuguste eeskirjade kohaselt selliste kindlustusseltside j&auml;relevalve, kelle emaettev&otilde;tja on kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja, edasikindlustusselts, kolmanda riigi kindlustusselts v&otilde;i segakindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja; kindlustusj&auml;relevalve juhtp&otilde;him&otilde;tteks j&auml;&auml;b p&auml;devate asutuste poolt &uuml;ksikkindlustusseltside &uuml;le teostatav j&auml;relevalve; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas it is necessary to calculate an adjusted solvency situation for insurance undertakings forming part of an insurance group; whereas different methods are applied by the competent authorities in the Community to take into account the effects on the financial situation of an insurance undertaking attributable to the fact that it belongs to an insurance group; whereas this Directive lays down three methods to effect that calculation; whereas the principle is accepted that these methods are prudentially equivalent; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) kindlustusandjate gruppi kuuluvate kindlustusseltside jaoks on vaja arvutada korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisus; &uuml;henduse p&auml;devad asutused kasutavad erinevaid meetodeid, et v&otilde;tta arvesse kindlustusandjate gruppi kuulumise m&otilde;ju kindlustusseltsi finantsseisundile; k&auml;esolevas direktiivis s&auml;testatakse sellise m&otilde;ju arvutamiseks kolm meetodit; tunnustatakse p&otilde;him&otilde;tet, et usaldatavusnormatiivide seisukohast on need meetodid samav&auml;&auml;rsed; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas the solvency of a related subsidiary insurance undertaking of an insurance holding company, reinsurance undertaking or non-member-country insurance undertaking may be affected by the financial resources of the group of which it is a part and by the distribution of financial resources within that group; whereas the competent authorities should be provided with the means of exercising supplementary supervision and of taking appropriate measures at the level of the insurance undertaking where its solvency is or may be jeopardised; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja, edasikindlustusseltsi, kolmanda riigi kindlustusseltsi sidust&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjast kindlustusseltsi maksej&otilde;ulisust v&otilde;ivad m&otilde;jutada selle grupi rahalised vahendid, millesse ta kuulub, ja rahaliste vahendite jaotamine k&otilde;nealuses grupis; p&auml;devatel asutustel peaks olema v&otilde;imalik teostada t&auml;iendavat j&auml;relevalvet ja v&otilde;tta vajalikke meetmeid selle kindlustusseltsi suhtes, kelle maksej&otilde;ulisus on ohus v&otilde;i v&otilde;ib ohtu sattuda; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas the competent authorities should have access to all the information relevant to the exercise of supplementary supervision; whereas cooperation between the authorities responsible for the supervision of insurance undertakings as well as between those authorities and the authorities responsible for the supervision of other financial sectors should be established; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) p&auml;devatel asutustel peaks olema juurdep&auml;&auml;s kogu teabele, mis on t&auml;iendava j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks vajalik; kindlustusseltside j&auml;relevalve eest vastutavate asutuste ning nimetatud asutuste ja muude finantssektorite j&auml;relevalve eest vastutavate asutuste vahel peaks toimuma koost&ouml;&ouml;; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) Whereas intra-group transactions can affect the financial position of an insurance undertaking; whereas the competent authorities should be in a position to exercise general supervision over certain types of such intra-group operations and take appropriate measures at the level of the insurance undertaking where its solvency is or may be jeopardised, </inglise>
<eesti> 11) grupisisesed tehingud v&otilde;ivad m&otilde;jutada kindlustusseltsi finantsseisundit; p&auml;devatel asutustel peaks olema v&otilde;imalik teostada &uuml;ldist j&auml;relevalvet selliste grupisiseste tehingute teatavate liikide &uuml;le ja v&otilde;tta vajalikke meetmeid selle kindlustusseltsi suhtes, kelle maksej&otilde;ulisus on ohus v&otilde;i v&otilde;ib ohtu sattuda, </eesti>
<inglise> HAVE ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Definitions </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) insurance undertaking means an undertaking which has received official authorisation in accordance with Article 6 of Directive 73/239/EEC or Article 6 of Directive 79/267/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> a) kindlustusselts - ettev&otilde;tja, kes on saanud ametliku tegevusloa vastavalt direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artiklile 6 v&otilde;i direktiivi 79/267/EM&Uuml; artiklile 6; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) non-member-country insurance undertaking means an undertaking which would require authorisation in accordance with Article 6 of Directive 73/239/EEC or Article 6 of Directive 79/267/EEC if it had its registered office in the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> b) kolmanda riigi kindlustusselts - ettev&otilde;tja, kellel peaks olema direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artiklile 6 v&otilde;i direktiivi 79/267/EM&Uuml; artiklile 6 vastav tegevusluba, kui tema registrij&auml;rgne asukoht oleks &uuml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) reinsurance undertaking means an undertaking, other than an insurance undertaking or a non-member-country insurance undertaking, the main business of which consists in accepting risks ceded by an insurance undertaking, a non-member-country insurance undertaking or other reinsurance undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti> c) edasikindlustusselts - ettev&otilde;tja, kes ei ole kindlustusselts ega kolmanda riigi kindlustusselts ja kelle p&otilde;hitegevus on v&otilde;tta vastu kindlustusseltside, kolmandate riikide kindlustusseltside v&otilde;i teiste edasikindlustusseltside loovutatud riske; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) parent undertaking means a parent undertaking within the meaning of Article 1 of Directive 83/349/EEC (8) and any undertaking which, in the opinion of the competent authorities, effectively exercises a dominant influence over another undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti> d) emaettev&otilde;tja - emaettev&otilde;tja direktiivi 83/349/EM&Uuml; (8) artikli 1 t&auml;henduses ja iga ettev&otilde;tja, kellel on p&auml;devate asutuste arvates valitsev m&otilde;ju m&otilde;ne teise ettev&otilde;tja &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) subsidiary undertaking means a subsidiary undertaking within the meaning of Article 1 of Directive 83/349/EEC and any undertaking over which, in the opinion of the competent authorities, a parent undertaking effectively exercises a dominant influence. </inglise>
<eesti> e) t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja - t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja direktiivi 83/349/EM&Uuml; artikli 1 t&auml;henduses ja iga ettev&otilde;tja, kelle &uuml;le emaettev&otilde;tjal on p&auml;devate asutuste arvates &uuml;lekaalukas m&otilde;ju. </eesti>
<inglise> All subsidiaries of subsidiary undertakings shall also be considered subsidiaries of the parent undertaking which is at the head of those undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;iki t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjate t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjaid k&auml;sitletakse samuti esialgse emaettev&otilde;tja t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjatena; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) participation means participation within the meaning of Article 17, first sentence, of Directive 78/660/EEC (9) or the holding, directly or indirectly, of 20 % or more of the voting rights or capital of an undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti> f) osalus - osalus direktiivi 78/660/EM&Uuml; (9) artikli 17 esimese lause t&auml;henduses v&otilde;i teatavas ettev&otilde;ttes v&auml;hemalt 20% h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i kapitali otsene v&otilde;i kaudne omamine; </eesti>
<inglise> (g) participating undertaking means an undertaking which is either a parent undertaking or another undertaking which holds a participation; </inglise>
<eesti> g) osalev ettev&otilde;tja - ettev&otilde;tja, kes on kas emaettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i m&otilde;ni muu ettev&otilde;tja, kellel on osalus; </eesti>
<inglise> (h) related undertaking means either a subsidiary or other undertaking in which a participation is held; </inglise>
<eesti> h) sidusettev&otilde;tja - t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i muu ettev&otilde;tja, kus on osalus; </eesti>
<inglise> (i) insurance holding company means a parent undertaking the main business of which is to acquire and hold participations in subsidiary undertakings, where those subsidiary undertakings are exclusively or mainly insurance undertakings, reinsurance undertakings or non-member-country insurance undertakings, one at least of such subsidiary undertakings being an insurance undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti> i) kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja - emaettev&otilde;tja, kelle peamine tegevus on osaluse soetamine ja valdamine t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjates, kes on ainult v&otilde;i peamiselt kindlustusseltsid, edasikindlustusseltsid v&otilde;i kolmandate riikide kindlustusseltsid ja kellest v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja on kindlustusselts; </eesti>
<inglise> (j) mixed-activity insurance holding company means a parent undertaking, other than an insurance undertaking, a non-member-country insurance undertaking, a reinsurance undertaking or an insurance holding company, which includes at least one insurance undertaking among its subsidiary undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti> j) segakindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja - emaettev&otilde;tja, kes ei ole kindlustusselts, kolmanda riigi kindlustusselts, edasikindlustusselts ega kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja ja kelle t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjate hulka kuulub v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kindlustusselts; </eesti>
<inglise> (k) competent authorities means the national authorities which are empowered by law or regulation to supervise insurance undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti> k) p&auml;devad asutused - liikmesriigi asutused, kelle p&auml;devusse on seaduse v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;rusega antud kindlustusseltside j&auml;relevalve. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Cases of application of supplementary supervision of insurance undertakings </inglise>
<eesti> Kindlustusseltside t&auml;iendava j&auml;relevalve kohaldamise juhud </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In addition to the provisions of Directives 73/239/EEC and 79/267/EEC which lay down the rules for the supervision of insurance undertakings, Member States shall provide supervision of any insurance undertaking which is a participating undertaking in at least one insurance undertaking, reinsurance undertaking, or non-member-country insurance undertaking shall be supplemented in the manner prescribed in Articles 5, 6, 8 and 9. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks direktiivide 73/239/EM&Uuml; ja 79/267/EM&Uuml; s&auml;tetele, millega on ette n&auml;htud kindlustusseltside j&auml;relevalve eeskirjad, s&auml;testavad liikmesriigid, et j&auml;relevalvet k&otilde;igi selliste kindlustusseltside &uuml;le, kes on osalev ettev&otilde;tja v&auml;hemalt &uuml;hes kindlustusseltsis, edasikindlustusseltsis v&otilde;i kolmanda riigi kindlustusseltsis, t&auml;iendatakse nii, nagu on kirjeldatud artiklites 5, 6, 8 ja 9. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Every insurance undertaking the parent undertaking of which is an insurance holding company, a reinsurance undertaking or a non-member-country insurance undertaking shall be subject to supplementary supervision in the manner prescribed in Articles 5(2), 6, 8 and 10. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;igi kindlustusseltside suhtes, kelle emaettev&otilde;tja on kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja, edasikindlustusselts v&otilde;i kolmanda riigi kindlustusselts, kohaldatakse t&auml;iendavat j&auml;relevalvet nii, nagu on s&auml;testatud artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 2 ning artiklites 6, 8 ja 10. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Every insurance undertaking the parent undertaking of which is a mixed-activity insurance holding company shall be subject to supplementary supervision in the manner prescribed in Articles 5(2), 6 and 8. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;igi kindlustusseltside suhtes, kelle emaettev&otilde;tja on segakindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja, kohaldatakse t&auml;iendavat j&auml;relevalvet nii, nagu on s&auml;testatud artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 2 ning artiklites 6 ja 8. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Scope of supplementary supervision </inglise>
<eesti> T&auml;iendava j&auml;relevalve ulatus </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The exercise of supplementary supervision in accordance with Article 2 shall in no way imply that the competent authorities are required to play a supervisory role in relation to the non-member-country insurance undertaking, insurance holding company or mixed-activity insurance holding company or reinsurance undertaking taken individually. </inglise>
<eesti> T&auml;iendav j&auml;relevalve artikli 2 t&auml;henduses ei t&auml;henda mingil juhul, et p&auml;devad asutused peavad teostama j&auml;relevalvet kolmandate riikide kindlustusseltside, kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tjate, segakindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tjate v&otilde;i edasikindlustusseltside &uuml;le eraldi. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The supplementary supervision shall take into account: </inglise>
<eesti> T&auml;iendava j&auml;relevalve alla kuuluvad: </eesti>
<inglise> - related undertakings of the insurance undertaking, </inglise>
<eesti> - kindlustusseltsi sidusettev&otilde;tjad, </eesti>
<inglise> - participating undertakings in the insurance undertaking, </inglise>
<eesti> - kindlustusseltsis osalevad ettev&otilde;tjad, </eesti>
<inglise> - related undertakings of a participating undertaking in the insurance undertaking, </inglise>
<eesti> - kindlustusseltsis osalevate ettev&otilde;tjate sidusettev&otilde;tjad, </eesti>
<inglise> referred to in Articles 5, 6, 8, 9 and 10. </inglise>
<eesti> keda on nimetatud artiklites 5, 6, 8, 9 ja 10. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may decide not to take into account in the supplementary supervision referred to in Article 2 undertakings having their registered office in a non-member country where there are legal impediments to the transfer of the necessary information, without prejudice to the provisions of Annex I, point 2.5, and of Annex II, point 4. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks I lisa punkti 2.5 ja II lisa punkti 4 kohaldamist, v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid otsustada, et artiklis 2 nimetatud t&auml;iendava j&auml;relevalve puhul ei v&otilde;eta arvesse ettev&otilde;tjaid, kelle registrij&auml;rgne asukoht on kolmandas riigis, kus vajaliku teabe edastamise suhtes kehtivad &otilde;iguslikud takistused. </eesti>
<inglise> Furthermore, the competent authorities responsible for exercising supplementary supervision may in the cases listed below decide on a case-by-case basis not to take an undertaking into account in the supplementary supervision referred to in Article 2: </inglise>
