<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Where, in applying this Article, the competent authorities of one Member State wish in specific cases to verify important information concerning an undertaking situated in another Member State which is a related insurance undertaking, a subsidiary undertaking, a parent undertaking or a subsidiary of a parent undertaking of the insurance undertaking subject to supplementary supervision, they must ask the competent authorities of that other Member State to have that verification carried out. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui &uuml;he liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused soovivad k&auml;esoleva artikli kohaldamisel kontrollida konkreetsetel juhtudel olulist teavet teises liikmesriigis asuva ettev&otilde;tja kohta, kes on t&auml;iendava j&auml;relevalve alla kuuluva kindlustusseltsi siduskindlustusselts, tema t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja, emaettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i emaettev&otilde;tja t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja, peavad nad kontrollimist taotlema k&otilde;nealuse teise liikmesriigi p&auml;devatelt asutustelt. </eesti>
<inglise> The authorities which receive such a request must act on it within the limits of their jurisdiction by carrying out the verification themselves, by allowing the authorities making the request to carry it out or by allowing an auditor or expert to carry it out. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutused, kes on sellise taotluse saanud, peavad oma p&auml;devuse piires teabe vastavust ise kontrollima v&otilde;i lubama seda teha kas taotluse esitanud asutustel, audiitoril v&otilde;i eksperdil. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Cooperation between competent authorities </inglise>
<eesti> Koost&ouml;&ouml; p&auml;devate asutuste vahel </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where insurance undertakings established in different Member States are directly or indirectly related or have a common participating undertaking, the competent authorities of each Member State shall communicate to one another on request all relevant information which may allow or facilitate the exercise of supervision pursuant to this Directive and shall communicate on their own initiative any information which appears to them to be essential for the other competent authorities. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui eri liikmesriikides asutatud kindlustusseltsid on omavahel otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt seotud v&otilde;i kui neil on sama osalev ettev&otilde;tja, edastavad iga liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused vastava taotluse korral &uuml;ksteisele kogu vajaliku teabe, mis v&otilde;imaldab k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohast t&auml;iendavat j&auml;relevalvet v&otilde;i aitab sellele kaasa, ja edastavad omal algatusel kogu teabe, mis on nende arvates teise p&auml;deva asutuse jaoks vajalik. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where an insurance undertaking and either a credit institution as defined in Directive 77/780/EEC (10) or an investment firm as defined in Directive 93/22/EEC (11), or both, are directly or indirectly related or have a common participating undertaking, the competent authorities and the authorities with public responsibility for the supervision of those other undertakings shall cooperate closely. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kindlustusselts on otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt seotud direktiivis 77/780/EM&Uuml; (10) m&auml;&auml;ratletud krediidiasutuse, direktiivis 93/22/EM&Uuml; (11) m&auml;&auml;ratletud investeerimis&uuml;hinguga v&otilde;i m&otilde;lemaga v&otilde;i kui neil on sama osalev ettev&otilde;tja, teevad p&auml;devad asutused ja muude nimetatud ettev&otilde;tjate riikliku j&auml;relevalve eest vastutavad asutused tihedat koost&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to their respective responsibilities, those authorities shall provide one another with any information likely to simplify their task, in particular within the framework of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud asutused edastavad &uuml;ksteisele teabe, mis v&otilde;iks nende t&ouml;&ouml;d lihtsustada eelk&otilde;ige k&auml;esoleva direktiivi raames, ilma et see piiraks nende vastavaid kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Information received pursuant to this Directive and, in particular, any exchange of information between competent authorities which is provided for in this Directive shall be subject to the obligation of professional secrecy defined in Article 16 of Directive 92/49/EEC and Article 15 of Directive 92/96/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt k&auml;esolevale direktiivile saadud teabe ja eriti k&auml;esolevas direktiivis s&auml;testatud p&auml;devate asutuste vahelise teabevahetuse puhul kehtib direktiivi 92/49/EM&Uuml; artiklis 16 ja direktiivi 92/96/EM&Uuml; artiklis 15 m&auml;&auml;ratletud ametisaladuse hoidmise kohustus. </eesti>
