<inglise> ANNEX I </inglise>
<eesti> I LISA </eesti>
<inglise> CALCULATION OF THE ADJUSTED SOLVENCY OF INSURANCE UNDERTAKINGS </inglise>
<eesti> KINDLUSTUSSELTSIDE KORRIGEERITUD MAKSEJ&Otilde;ULISUSE ARVUTAMINE </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> CHOICE OF CALCULATION METHOD AND GENERAL PRINCIPLES </inglise>
<eesti> ARVUTUSMEETODI VALIK JA &Uuml;LDP&Otilde;HIM&Otilde;TTED </eesti>
<inglise> A. Member States shall provide that the calculation of the adjusted solvency of insurance undertakings referred to in Article 2(1) shall be carried out according to one of the methods described in point 3. </inglise>
<eesti> A. Liikmesriigid n&auml;evad ette, et artikli 2 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kindlustusseltside korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisuse arvutamine toimub &uuml;he punktis 3 kirjeldatud meetodi kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> A Member State may, however, provide for the competent authorities to authorise or impose the application of a method set out in point 3 other than that chosen by the Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriik v&otilde;ib siiski ette n&auml;ha, et p&auml;devad asutused annavad loa kasutada v&otilde;i kohustavad kasutama muud punktis 3 s&auml;testatud meetodit kui seda, mille valis liikmesriik. </eesti>
<inglise> B. Proportionality </inglise>
<eesti> B. Proportsionaalsus </eesti>
<inglise> The calculation of the adjusted solvency of an insurance undertaking shall take account of the proportional share held by the participating undertaking in its related undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti> Kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisuse arvutamisel v&otilde;etakse arvesse osaleva ettev&otilde;tja suhtelist osa tema sidusettev&otilde;tjates. </eesti>
<inglise> 'Proportional share' means either, where method 1 or method 2 described in point 3 is used, the proportion of the subscribed capital that is held, directly or indirectly, by the participating undertaking or, where method 3 described in point 3 is used, the percentages used for the establishment of the consolidated accounts. </inglise>
<eesti> "Suheline osa" t&auml;hendab punktis 3 kirjeldatud meetodite 1 ja 2 kasutamise puhul otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt osalevale ettev&otilde;tjale kuuluva m&auml;rgitud kapitali osa suurust ja punktis 3 kirjeldatud meetodi 3 kasutamise puhul konsolideeritud aastaaruannete koostamisel kasutatud protsendim&auml;&auml;rasid. </eesti>
<inglise> However, whichever method is used, when the related undertaking is a subsidiary undertaking and has a solvency deficit, the total solvency deficit of the subsidiary has to be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui sidusettev&otilde;tja on t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja ja tema maksej&otilde;ulisus on puudulik, tuleb olenemata kasutatud meetodist siiski arvesse v&otilde;tta t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja kogu maksej&otilde;ulisuse puuduj&auml;&auml;k. </eesti>
<inglise> However, where, in the opinion of the competent authorities, the responsibility of the parent undertaking owning a share of the capital is limited strictly and unambiguously to that share of the capital, such competent authorities may give permission for the solvency deficit of the subsidiary undertaking to be taken into account on a proportional basis. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui p&auml;devate asutuste arvates piirdub kapitali osa omava emaettev&otilde;tja vastutus kindlalt ja &uuml;heselt ainult nimetatud kapitali osaga, v&otilde;ivad need p&auml;devad asutused anda loa, mille kohaselt t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja maksej&otilde;ulisuse puuduj&auml;&auml;gi v&otilde;ib arvesse v&otilde;tta proportsionaalsel alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> C. Elimination of double use of solvency margin elements </inglise>
<eesti> C. Solventsusmarginaali elementide topeltkasutamise v&auml;listamine </eesti>
<inglise> C.1. General treatment of solvency margin elements </inglise>
<eesti> C.1. Solventsusmarginaali elementide &uuml;ldine k&auml;sitlemine </eesti>
<inglise> Regardless of the method used for the calculation of the adjusted solvency of an insurance undertaking, the double use of elements eligible for the solvency margin among the different insurance undertakings taken into account in that calculation must be eliminated. </inglise>
<eesti> Olenemata kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisuse arvutamisel kasutatud meetodist, tuleb v&auml;listada solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivate elementide topeltkasutamine arvutamisel arvessev&otilde;etud eri kindlustusseltside seas. </eesti>
<inglise> For this purpose, when calculating the adjusted solvency of an insurance undertaking and where the methods described in point 3 do not provide for it, the following amounts shall be eliminated: </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks tuleb kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisuse arvutamisel ja juhul, kui seda ei ole ette n&auml;htud punktis 3 kirjeldatud meetoditega, v&auml;lja j&auml;tta j&auml;rgmised summad: </eesti>
<inglise> - the value of any asset of that insurance undertaking which represents the financing of elements eligible for the solvency margin of one of its related insurance undertakings, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;nealuse kindlustusseltsi k&otilde;igi selliste varade v&auml;&auml;rtus, mida kasutatakse &uuml;he temaga seotud kindlustusseltsi solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivate elementide finantseerimiseks, </eesti>
<inglise> - the value of any asset of a related insurance undertaking of that insurance undertaking which represents the financing of elements eligible for the solvency margin of that insurance undertaking, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;nealuse kindlustusseltsiga seotud kindlustusseltsi k&otilde;igi selliste varade v&auml;&auml;rtus, mida kasutatakse k&otilde;nealuse kindlustusseltsi solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivate elementide finantseerimiseks, </eesti>
<inglise> - the value of any asset of a related insurance undertaking of that insurance undertaking which represents the financing of elements eligible for the solvency margin of any other related insurance undertaking of that insurance undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;nealuse kindlustusseltsiga seotud kindlustusseltsi k&otilde;igi selliste varade v&auml;&auml;rtus, mida kasutatakse m&otilde;ne muu k&otilde;nealuse kindlustusseltsiga seotud kindlustusseltsi solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivate elementide finantseerimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> C.2. Treatment of certain elements </inglise>
<eesti> C.2. Teatavate elementide k&auml;sitlemine </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to the provisions of section C.1: </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks punkti C.1 s&auml;tete kohaldamist: </eesti>
<inglise> - profit reserves and future profits arising in a related life assurance undertaking of the insurance undertaking for which the adjusted solvency is calculated, and </inglise>
<eesti> - kindlustusseltsiga, mille korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisust arvutatakse, seotud elukindlustusseltsi kasumireserve ja edaspidist kasumit ja </eesti>
<inglise> - any subscribed but not paid-up capital of a related insurance undertaking of the insurance undertaking for which the adjusted solvency is calculated, </inglise>
<eesti> - kindlustusseltsiga, mille korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisust arvutatakse, seotud kindlustusseltsi m&auml;rgitud, kuid sissemaksmata kapitali, </eesti>
<inglise> may only be included in the calculation in so far as they are eligible for covering the solvency margin requirement of that related undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ib arvutamisel arvesse v&otilde;tta, kui nad sobivad k&otilde;nealuse sidusettev&otilde;tja n&otilde;utava solventsusmarginaali katmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> However, any subscribed but not paid-up capital which represents a potential obligation on the part of the participating undertaking shall be entirely excluded from the calculation. </inglise>
<eesti> Arvutusest j&auml;etakse t&auml;iesti v&auml;lja igasugune m&auml;rgitud, kuid sissemaksmata kapital, mille puhul on tegemist osaleva ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;imaliku kohustusega. </eesti>
<inglise> Any subscribed but not paid-up capital of the participating insurance undertaking which represents a potential obligation on the part of a related insurance undertaking shall also be excluded from the calculation. </inglise>
<eesti> Arvutusest j&auml;etakse t&auml;iesti v&auml;lja ka igasugune osaleva kindlustusseltsi m&auml;rgitud, kuid sissemaksmata kapital, mille puhul on tegemist seotud kindlustusseltsi v&otilde;imaliku kohustusega. </eesti>
<inglise> Any subscribed but not paid-up capital of a related insurance undertaking which represents a potential obligation on the part of another related insurance undertaking of the same participating insurance undertaking shall be excluded from the calculation. </inglise>
<eesti> Arvutusest j&auml;etakse t&auml;iesti v&auml;lja igasugune seotud kindlustusseltsi m&auml;rgitud, kuid sissemaksmata kapital, mille puhul on tegemist sama osaleva kindlustusseltsiga seotud m&otilde;ne teise kindlustusseltsi v&otilde;imaliku kohustusega. </eesti>
<inglise> C.3. Transferability </inglise>
<eesti> C.3. &Uuml;lekandmine </eesti>
<inglise> If the competent authorities consider that certain elements eligible for the solvency margin of a related insurance undertaking other than those referred to in section C.2 cannot effectively be made available to cover the solvency margin requirement of the participating insurance undertaking for which the adjusted solvency is calculated, those elements may be included in the calculation only in so far as they are eligible for covering the solvency margin requirement of the related undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui p&auml;devad asutused leiavad, et teatavad seotud kindlustusseltsi solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivad elemendid, mida ei nimetatud punktis C.2, ei ole selle osaleva kindlustusseltsi, mille korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisust arvutatakse, n&otilde;utava solventsusmarginaali katmiseks tegelikult kasutatavad, v&otilde;ib k&otilde;nealuseid elemente arvutamisel arvesse v&otilde;tta ainult niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd nad sobivad sidusettev&otilde;tja n&otilde;utava solventusmarginaali katmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> C.4. The sum of the elements referred to in sections C.2 and C.3 may not exceed the solvency margin requirement of the related insurance undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti> C.4. Punktides C.2 ja C.3 nimetatud elementide summa ei v&otilde;i olla suurem kui seotud kindlustusseltsi n&otilde;utav solventusmarginaal. </eesti>
<inglise> D. Elimination of the intra-group creation of capital </inglise>
<eesti> D. Grupisisese kapitali v&auml;listamine </eesti>
<inglise> When calculating adjusted solvency, no account shall be taken of any element eligible for the solvency margin arising out of reciprocal financing between the insurance undertaking and: </inglise>
<eesti> Korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisuse arvutamisel ei v&otilde;eta arvesse solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivaid elemente, mis p&auml;rinevad vastastikusest finantseerimisest kindlustusseltsi ja: </eesti>
<inglise> - a related undertaking, </inglise>
<eesti> - sidusettev&otilde;tja, </eesti>
<inglise> - a participating undertaking, </inglise>
<eesti> - osaleva ettev&otilde;tja, </eesti>
<inglise> - another related undertaking of any of its participating undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti> - m&otilde;ne selles osaleva ettev&otilde;tja teise sidusettev&otilde;tja vahel. </eesti>
<inglise> Furthermore, no account shall be taken of any element eligible for the solvency margin of a related insurance undertaking of the insurance undertaking for which the adjusted solvency is calculated when the element in question arises out of reciprocal financing with any other related undertaking of that insurance undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks sellele ei v&otilde;eta arvesse &uuml;htegi sellise kindlustusseltsiga, mille korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisust arvutatakse, seotud kindlustusseltsi solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivat elementi, kui k&otilde;nealune element on p&auml;rit vastastikusest finantseerimisest k&otilde;nealuse kindlustusseltsi m&otilde;ne muu sidusettev&otilde;tjaga. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, reciprocal financing exists when an insurance undertaking, or any of its related undertakings, holds shares in, or makes loans to, another undertaking which, directly or indirectly, holds an element eligible for the solvency margin of the first undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastastikuse finantseerimisega on tegu eelk&otilde;ige siis, kui kindlustusseltsile v&otilde;i m&otilde;nele tema sidusettev&otilde;tjatest kuuluvad teise ettev&otilde;tja aktsiad v&otilde;i kui ta annab sellele laenu ja k&otilde;nealusele ettev&otilde;tjale kuulub otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt esimese ettev&otilde;tja solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobiv element. </eesti>
<inglise> E. The competent authorities shall ensure that the adjusted solvency is calculated with the same frequency as that laid down by Directives 73/239/EEC and 79/267/EEC for calculating the solvency margin of insurance undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti> E. P&auml;devad asutused tagavad, et korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisus arvutatakse sama sageli, nagu direktiividega 73/239/EM&Uuml; ja 79/267/EM&Uuml; on ette n&auml;htud kindlustusseltside solventsusmarginaali arvutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> The value of the assets and liabilities shall be assessed according to the relevant provisions of Directives 73/239/EEC, 79/267/EEC and 91/674/EEC (1). </inglise>
<eesti> Varade ja kohustuste v&auml;&auml;rtust hinnatakse vastavalt direktiivide 73/239/EM&Uuml;, 79/267/EM&Uuml; ja 91/674/EM&Uuml; (1) asjaomastele s&auml;tetele. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> APPLICATION OF THE CALCULATION METHODS </inglise>
<eesti> ARVUTUSMEETODITE KOHALDAMINE </eesti>
<inglise> 2.1. </inglise>
<eesti> 2.1. </eesti>
<inglise> Related insurance undertakings </inglise>
<eesti> Seotud kindlustusseltsid </eesti>
<inglise> The adjusted solvency calculation shall be carried out in accordance with the general principles and methods set out in this Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisus arvutatakse k&auml;esolevas lisas s&auml;testatud &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tete ja meetodite kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> In the case of all methods, where the insurance undertaking has more than one related insurance undertaking, the adjusted solvency calculation shall be carried out by integrating each of these related insurance undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kindlustusseltsil on rohkem kui &uuml;ks sidusettev&otilde;tja, arvutatakse korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisus k&otilde;igi meetodite puhul selliselt, et arvesse v&otilde;etakse k&otilde;ik k&otilde;nealused seotud kindlustusseltsid. </eesti>
<inglise> In cases of successive participations (for example, where an insurance undertaking is a participating undertaking in another insurance undertaking which is also a participating undertaking in an insurance undertaking), the adjusted solvency calculation shall be carried out at the level of each participating insurance undertaking which has at least one related insurance undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti> J&auml;rjestikuste osaluste puhul (n&auml;iteks siis, kui kindlustusselts on osalev ettev&otilde;tja teises kindlustusseltsis, kes on omakorda osalev ettev&otilde;tja m&otilde;nes kindlustusseltsis) arvutatakse korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisus iga osaleva kindlustusseltsi puhul, kellel on v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks seotud kindlustusselts. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may waive calculation of the adjusted solvency of an insurance undertaking: </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad loobuda kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisuse arvutamisest, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> - if the undertaking is a related undertaking of another insurance undertaking authorised in the same Member State, and that related undertaking is taken into account in the calculation of the adjusted solvency of the participating insurance undertaking, or </inglise>
<eesti> - ettev&otilde;tja on teise samas liikmesriigis tegevusloa saanud kindlustusseltsi sidusettev&otilde;tja ja nimetatud sidusettev&otilde;tjat on arvestatud osaleva kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisuse arvutamisel v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - if the insurance undertaking is a related undertaking either of an insurance holding company or of a reinsurance undertaking which has its registered office in the same Member State as the insurance undertaking, and both the holding insurance company or the reinsurance undertaking and the related insurance undertaking are taken into account in the calculation carried out. </inglise>
<eesti> - kindlustusselts on kas kindlustusseltsiga samas liikmesriigis registrij&auml;rgse asukohaga kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i edasikindlustusseltsi sidusettev&otilde;tja ning nii kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tjat v&otilde;i edasikindlustusseltsi kui ka seotud kindlustusseltsi v&otilde;etakse arvutamisel arvesse. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may also waive calculation of the adjusted solvency of an insurance undertaking if it is a related insurance undertaking of another insurance undertaking, a reinsurance undertaking or an insurance holding company which has its registered office in another Member State, and if the competent authorities of the Member States concerned have agreed to grant exercise of the supplementary supervision to the competent authority of the latter Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisuse arvutamisest loobuda ka siis, kui kindlustusselts on m&otilde;nes muus liikmesriigis registrij&auml;rgse asukohaga teise kindlustusseltsi, edasikindlustusseltsi v&otilde;i kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja sidusettev&otilde;tja ja kui asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused on andnud n&otilde;usoleku loovutada t&auml;iendav j&auml;relevalve asukohariigi p&auml;devale asutusele. </eesti>
<inglise> In each case, the waiver may be granted only if the competent authorities are satisfied that the elements eligible for the solvency margins of the insurance undertakings included in the calculation are adequately distributed between those undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti> Arvutamisest v&otilde;ib igal juhul loobuda &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui arvutamisel arvessev&otilde;etavate kindlustusseltside solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivad elemendid on p&auml;devate asutuste arvates k&otilde;nealuste ettev&otilde;tjate vahel n&otilde;uetekohaselt jaotatud. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may provide that where the related insurance undertaking has its registered office in a Member State other than that of the insurance undertaking for which the adjusted solvency calculation is carried out, the calculation shall take account, in respect of the related undertaking, of the solvency situation as assessed by the competent authorities of that other Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad ette n&auml;ha, et juhul, kui seotud kindlustusseltsi registrij&auml;rgne asukoht ei ole samas liikmesriigis, kus asub kindlustusselts, mille korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisust arvutatakse, v&otilde;etakse sidusettev&otilde;tja maksej&otilde;u puhul arvutamisel arvesse k&otilde;nealuse teise liikmesriigi p&auml;devate asutuste hinnangut maksej&otilde;u kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> 2.2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2.2. </eesti>
<inglise> Related reinsurance undertakings </inglise>
<eesti> Seotud edasikindlustusseltsid </eesti>
<inglise> When calculating the adjusted solvency of an insurance undertaking which is a participating undertaking in a reinsurance undertaking, this related reinsurance undertaking shall be treated, solely for the purposes of the calculation, by analogy with a related insurance undertaking, applying the general principles and methods described in this Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui arvutatakse edasikindlustusseltsis osalevast ettev&otilde;tjast kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisust, k&auml;sitletakse k&otilde;nealust seotud edasikindlustusseltsi ainult arvutamisel analoogiliselt seotud kindlustusseltsiga, kohaldades k&auml;esolevas lisas kirjeldatud &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tteid ja meetodeid. </eesti>
<inglise> To this end, a notional solvency requirement shall be established for each related reinsurance undertaking on the basis of the same rules as are laid down in Article 16(2) to (5) of Directive 73/239/EEC or Article 19 of Directive 79/267/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks kehtestatakse iga seotud edasikindlustusseltsi jaoks teoreetilise maksej&otilde;ulisuse n&otilde;ue vastavalt samadele eeskirjadele, mis on s&auml;testatud direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artikli 16 l&otilde;igetes 2-5 v&otilde;i direktiivi 79/267/EM&Uuml; artiklis 19. </eesti>
<inglise> However, in the event of significant difficulty in applying these rules, the competent authorities may permit the notional life solvency requirement to be calculated on the basis of the first result as set out in Article 16(3) of Directive 73/239/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui nimetatud eeskirjade kohaldamisega peaksid kaasnema m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rsed raskused, v&otilde;ivad p&auml;devad asutused lubada, et elukindlustuse teoreetiline maksej&otilde;ulisus arvutatakse esimese tulemuse p&otilde;hjal, nagu on s&auml;testatud direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artikli 16 l&otilde;ikes 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The same elements as are found in Article 16(1) of Directive 73/239/EEC and in Article 18 of Directive 79/267/EEC shall be recognised as eligible for the notional solvency margin. </inglise>
<eesti> Teoreetilise solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivana k&auml;sitletakse samu elemente, mis on s&auml;testatud direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artikli 16 l&otilde;ikes 1 ja direktiivi 79/267/EM&Uuml; artiklis 18. </eesti>
<inglise> The value of the assets and liabilities shall be assessed according to the same rules as are laid down in those Directives and in Directive 91/674/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> Varade ja kohustuste v&auml;&auml;rtust hinnatakse samade eeskirjade kohaselt, mis on s&auml;testatud nimetatud direktiivides ja direktiivis 91/674/EM&Uuml;. </eesti>
<inglise> 2.3. </inglise>
<eesti> 2.3. </eesti>
<inglise> Intermediate insurance holding companies </inglise>
<eesti> Vahendavad kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tjad </eesti>
<inglise> When calculating the adjusted solvency of an insurance undertaking which holds a participation in an insurance undertaking, a related reinsurance undertaking, or an insurance undertaking in a non-member country through an insurance holding company, the situation of the intermediate insurance holding company is taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui arvutatakse sellise kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisust, kellele kuulub kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja vahendusel osalus edasikindlustusseltsis, seotud kindlustusseltsis v&otilde;i kolmanda riigi kindlustusseltsis, v&otilde;etakse vahendava kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tja seisundit arvesse. </eesti>
<inglise> For the sole purpose of this calculation, to be undertaken in accordance with the general principles and methods described in this Annex, this insurance holding company shall be treated as if it were an insurance undertaking subject to a zero solvency requirement and were subject to the same conditions as are laid down in Article 16(1) of Directive 73/239/EEC or in Article 18 of Directive 79/267/EEC in respect of elements eligible for the solvency margin. </inglise>
<eesti> Ainult k&auml;esolevas lisas kirjeldatud &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tete ja meetodite kohase arvutamise eesm&auml;rgil k&auml;sitletakse k&otilde;nealust kindlustusvaldusettev&otilde;tjat nii, nagu oleks tema n&auml;ol tegemist kindlustusseltsiga, kelle puhul kehtib maksej&otilde;ulisuse nulln&otilde;ue ja kelle suhtes kohaldatakse samu tingimusi, nagu on direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artikli 16 l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i direktiivi 79/267/EM&Uuml; artiklis 18 s&auml;testatud seoses solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivate elementidega. </eesti>
<inglise> 2.4. </inglise>
<eesti> 2.4. </eesti>
<inglise> Related insurance or reinsurance undertakings having their registered office in non-member countries </inglise>
<eesti> Seotud kindlustusseltsid v&otilde;i edasikindlustusseltsid, kelle registrij&auml;rgne asukoht on kolmandas riigis </eesti>
<inglise> A. Related non-member country insurance undertakings </inglise>
<eesti> A. Kolmandate riikide seotud kindlustusseltsid </eesti>
<inglise> When calculating the adjusted solvency of an insurance undertaking which is a participating undertaking in a non-member-country insurance undertaking, the latter shall be treated solely for the purposes of the calculation, by analogy with a related insurance undertaking, by applying the general principles and methods described in this Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui arvutatakse kolmanda riigi kindlustusseltsis osalevast ettev&otilde;tjast kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisust, k&auml;sitletakse k&otilde;nealust kolmanda riigi kindlustusseltsi ainult arvutamisega seotud eesm&auml;rkidel analoogiliselt seotud kindlustusseltsiga, kohaldades k&auml;esolevas lisas kirjeldatud &uuml;ldisi p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid ja meetodeid. </eesti>
<inglise> However, where the non-member-country in which that undertaking has its registered office makes it subject to authorisation and imposes on it a solvency requirement at least comparable to that laid down in Directives 73/239/EEC or 79/267/EEC, taking into account the elements of cover of that requirement, Member States may provide that the calculation shall take into account, as regards that undertaking, the solvency requirement and the elements eligible to satisfy that requirement as laid down by the non-member country in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kolmas riik, kus on k&otilde;nealuse kindlustusseltsi registrij&auml;rgne asukoht, n&otilde;uab sellise tegevuse puhul tegevusluba ja kehtestab maksej&otilde;ulisuse n&otilde;ude, mis on v&auml;hemalt v&otilde;rreldav direktiivides 73/239/EM&Uuml; v&otilde;i 79/267/EM&Uuml; s&auml;testatuga, v&otilde;ttes arvesse nimetatud n&otilde;ude katteelemente, v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid s&auml;testada, et arvutamisel v&otilde;etakse k&otilde;nealuse ettev&otilde;tja puhul arvesse maksej&otilde;ulisuse n&otilde;uet ja nimetatud n&otilde;ude jaoks sobivaid elemente, nii nagu k&otilde;nealuse kolmas riik on s&auml;testanud. </eesti>
<inglise> B. Related non-member-country reinsurance undertakings </inglise>
<eesti> B. Kolmandate riikide seotud edasikindlustusseltsid </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding section 2.2, when calculating the adjusted solvency of an insurance undertaking which is a participating undertaking in a reinsurance undertaking with its registered office in a non-member country, and subject to the same conditions as those set out in point A above, Member States may provide that the calculation shall take account, as regards the latter undertaking, of the own-funds requirement and the elements eligible to satisfy that requirement as laid down by the non-member country in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui arvutatakse kolmandas riigis paikneva registrij&auml;rgse asukohaga edasikindlustusseltsis osalevast ettev&otilde;tjast kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisust, tehes seda samadel tingimustel, mis on s&auml;testatud punktis A, v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid olenemata punktist 2.2 s&auml;testada, et arvutamisel v&otilde;etakse k&otilde;nealuse edasikindlustusseltsi puhul arvesse omavahendite n&otilde;uet ja nimetatud n&otilde;ude jaoks sobivaid elemente nii, nagu k&otilde;nealune kolmas riik on s&auml;testanud. </eesti>
<inglise> Where only the insurance undertakings of that non-member country are subject to such provisions, the notional own-funds requirement on the related reinsurance undertaking and the elements eligible to satisfy that notional requirement may be calculated as if the undertaking in question were a related insurance undertaking of that non-member country. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui selliseid s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse ainult k&otilde;nealuse kolmanda riigi kindlustusseltside suhtes, v&otilde;ib seotud kindlustusseltsi teoreetilise omavahendite n&otilde;ude ja nimetatud teoreetilise n&otilde;ude jaoks sobivad elemendid arvutada nii, nagu oleks k&otilde;nealune ettev&otilde;tja k&otilde;nealuse kolmanda riigi seotud kindlustusselts. </eesti>
<inglise> 2.5. </inglise>
<eesti> 2.5. </eesti>
<inglise> Non-availability of the necessary information </inglise>
<eesti> Vajaliku teabe puudumine </eesti>
<inglise> Where information necessary for calculating the adjusted solvency of an insurance undertaking, concerning a related undertaking with its registered office in a Member State or a non-member country, is not available to the competent authorities, for whatever reason, the book value of that undertaking in the participating insurance undertaking shall be deducted from the elements eligible for the adjusted solvency margin. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kindlustusseltsi korrigeeritud maksej&otilde;ulisuse arvutamiseks vajalik teave liikmesriigis v&otilde;i kolmandas riigis oleva registrij&auml;rgse asukohaga sidusettev&otilde;tja kohta ei ole mingil p&otilde;hjusel p&auml;devatele asutustele k&auml;ttesaadav, arvatakse k&otilde;nealuse ettev&otilde;tja bilansiline v&auml;&auml;rtus osalevas kindlustusseltsis maha korrigeeritud solventsusmarginaali jaoks sobivatest elementidest. </eesti>
<inglise> In that case, the unrealised gains connected with such participation shall not be allowed as an element eligible for the adjusted solvency margin. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellisel juhul ei peeta sellise osalusega seotud realiseerimata kasumit korrigeeritud solventsusmarginaali sobivaks elemendiks. </eesti>
